# Frontend Edit Mode Conventions

## Hook pattern (one per edit mode)

Each mode (Add, Delete, Copy, Modify) gets a dedicated `useXxxSlot` hook in `src/hooks/`. Pattern:

- **Local state** for interactive preview (high-frequency updates like mouse tracking)
- **Redux dispatch** only on commit (confirmed action)
- Hook returns: `isXxxMode`, `handleMapClick`, `handleMouseMove`, `handleKeyDown`, `toggleXxxMode`
- Shared geometry lives in `src/utils/slot-geometry.ts` — never duplicate math in hooks

## Mutual exclusion

All mode toggles go through `App.tsx`'s `enterMode(toggle)` which calls `exitCurrentMode()` first. Never activate two modes simultaneously.

## MapPanel layers — no double rendering

- `slots-fill` (opacity 0) exists solely for click/hover hit detection via `interactiveLayerIds`
- `slots-line` shows source-colored outlines **only when no overlay covers them** (set `line-opacity: 0` when postprocess overlay is active)
- Overlay layers (`overlay-postprocess-*`, `overlay-detection-*`, `overlay-mask-*`) are conditionally mounted — never stack them with `slots-line`
- One-slot feedback layers (`selected-slot`, `hovered-slot`, `pending-bbox`, `modifying-bbox`) are always safe — they show a single slot

## MapPanel click passthrough

When `isEditMode` is true, `handleClick` must forward to `onMapClick` immediately — never swallow clicks for popups. Popups only show in browse mode (`editMode === 'none'`).

## Redux edit history

All slot mutations (`addSlot`, `deleteSlot`, `modifySlot`) must call `truncateFuture(state)` before pushing to `editHistory`, then increment `editIndex`. This keeps undo/redo consistent.
